claim.claim-text:
6. An apparatus, comprising:
a first optical transmitter transmitting a first optical signal;
a first optical switch having an input that receives the first optical signal, and first and second outputs, the optical switch selectively supplying the first optical signal to one of the first and second outputs, the first output being coupled to a first optical communication path;
a second optical switch having first and second inputs and an output, the first input of the second optical switch being coupled to the second output of the first optical switch and the second input of the second optical switch being coupled to a second optical communication path,
an optical receiver configured to receive the first optical signal from the output of the second optical switch when the first optical signal is supplied from the second output of the first optical switch to the first input of the second optical switch;
a second optical transmitter supplying a second optical signal to the second optical communication path, such that the output of the second optical switch supplies the second optical signal to the optical receiver when the first optical switch does not supply the first optical signal to the first input of the second optical switch,
Wherein the first optical receiver includes a digital signal processor configured to supply an output signal indicative of a phase and amplitude of the first optical signal, the apparatus further including
a processor circuit configured to supply a control signal in response to the output signal from the digital signal processor, the first optical transmitter receiving the control signal, such that the phase and the amplitude of the first optical signal is adjusted in response to the control signal.
